MemoryObject - Interface in memory
MemoryObject is an interface that must be implemented if you want your object to be able to be reused.
MemoryPool<E extends MemoryObject> - Class in memory
The MemoryPool is the structure that contains all objects in the pool of memory. It is implemented using an array to stock the objects, and a stack to stock the indices of free objects, i.e their position in the array.

mul(MDD, BigInteger, BigInteger, int, Domains) - Static method in class builder.MDDBuilder
This method return a MDD which respect the multiplicative constraint
The multiplicative constraint ensure that if we multiply all the variables together, the result belong to the interval [m_min, m_max].
